<h1 id="overview">Overview</h1>
<p>Thank you for purchasing our <strong>Blog for PrestaShop</strong> module.</p>
<p>If you have any questions that are beyond the scope of this help file, please feel free to contact us using our support system <a href="./here">http://prestahome.ticksy.com/</a>.</p>
<p>This module is compatible with PrestaShop 1.6 and 1.7, though we do have a PrestaShop 1.5 version in our package we are not supporting it any longer.</p>
<p><img alt="Preview" src="./img/lead_banner.png" /></p>
<h2 id="whats-inside-package">What's inside package?</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>documentation</code> - this documentation,</li>
<li><code>For PrestaShop 1.5</code> - module for PrestaShop 1.5, we are no longer supporting this version,</li>
<li><code>For PrestaShop 1.6</code> - <strong>always</strong> newest version of the module for PrestaShop 1.6 <strong>and all compatible widgets</strong></li>
<li><code>For PrestaShop 1.7</code> - <strong>always</strong> newest version of the module for PrestaShop 1.7 <strong>and all compatible widgets</strong></li>
</ul>
<h2 id="what-are-widgets">What are <em>widgets</em>?</h2>
<p>Additional modules, for example to display recent blog posts on homepage of your store, add related posts to products (and the other way around), custom block with posts etc.</p>
<h1 id="how-to-install-module">How to install module?</h1>
<p>Our module is fully compatible with the default PrestaShop module installation method, all what you need to do is upload a module, install, and configure it.</p>
<h2 id="instruction">Instruction</h2>
<p>First method: Installation from back-office (recommended)</p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to Modules -&gt; Modules.</li>
<li>Click "Add new" button on the top right corner, or "Upload" in case you're using PrestaShop 1.7.</li>
<li>Now you may see upload form, please select <code>ph_simpleblog.zip</code> from your disk.</li>
<li>Confirm your choice, upload module.</li>
<li>Find Blog for PrestaShop on your modules list, just type "blog" on search form and you should see your new module.</li>
<li>Install/Configure module.</li>
</ol>
<p>Second method: Manual upload on server and install from back-office</p>
<ol>
<li>Connect with your server.</li>
<li>Navigate to /modules/ folder in your PrestaShop folder structure.</li>
<li>Unzip ph_simpleblog.zip and upload ph_simpleblog folder to your server.</li>
<li>The path should be like this: /modules/ph_simpleblog/ph_simpleblog.php</li>
<li>Now go to your back-office.</li>
<li>Navigate to Modules -&gt; Modules</li>
<li>Find Blog for PrestaShop on your modules list, just type "blog" on search form and you should see your new module.</li>
<li>Click "Install" button.</li>
</ol>
<p>After installation you should see new Tab in your back-office called Blog for PrestaShop.</p>
<h2 id="upgrading">Upgrading</h2>
<p>How tu upgrade Blog for PrestaShop?</p>
<p>If you have downloaded new version of the module frome CodeCanyon that is what you should do:</p>
<ol>
<li>Unzip files.</li>
<li>Find ph_simpleblog.zip and other "widgets" which are for your PrestaShop version</li>
<li>Follow instruction from "Installation" section </li>
<li>You should have updated module right after upload new files on your server and navigate to Modules tab.</li>
</ol>
<p>This method works for main module and widgets too.</p>
<p>PrestaShop have quite amazing upgrade method in 1.5 version and newer, so everytime when you download update from CodeCanyon, the update will be the same as the installation and the module dont lose any of your settings, posts etc.!</p>
<p>If anything changes we will definitely write about that in the update guide.</p>
<h2 id="custom-css-or-javascript">Custom CSS or JavaScript</h2>
<p>You can add your custom CSS code by going to Blog for PrestaShop -&gt; Custom CSS</p>
<h1 id="new-in-prestashop">New in PrestaShop?</h1>
<p>If you haven't work with PrestaShop before take a look at the docs available here: <a href="http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS16/User+Guide">http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS16/User+Guide</a></p>
<p>or for PrestaShop 1.7: <a href="http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS17/User+Guide">http://doc.prestashop.com/display/PS17/User+Guide</a></p>
<h1 id="faq">FAQ</h1>
